article.description: Trevor Mbakwe scored 22 of his 24 points in the second half and Minnesota (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today) snapped a four-game losing streak by pounding Iowa 62-45 Sunday.
article.headline: Trevor Mbakwe's 22-point second-half outburst helps Minnesota crush Iowa
article.linkText: Mbakwe explodes after half  in Minnesota's rout
article.story: IOWA CITY, Iowa -- Trevor Mbakwe scored 22 of his 24 points in the second half and Minnesota (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today) snapped a four-game losing streak by pounding Iowa 62-45 Sunday. Rodney Williams added 13 points for the Gophers (17-8, 6-7 Big Ten), who put an end to their longest skid under coach Tubby Smith by dominating the once-surging Hawkeyes. Minnesota erased an early deficit with a 24-6 run to end the first half. Mbakwe's layup and jumper pushed the Gophers' lead to 38-23, and Minnesota extended the margin to 48-27 with 8:01 to play. Bryce Cartwright had 11 points and seven assists to lead Iowa (10-15, 3-10), which shot just 34 percent from the floor and 21 percent (6 of 28) from 3-point range.
